The paper deals with problems related to graph theory and parameterized complexity. Specifically, it focuses on two problems, Strong Triadic Closure and Cluster Deletion, which are both related to the presence of induced $P_3$s in undirected graphs. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the fixed-parameter tractability of the problems, which is a common topic in Parameterized Complexity (cs.GT) research. The paper also mentions the classical complexity of the problems on $H$-free graphs, which could place it in the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) category. Finally, the paper's focus on graph labeling and induced subgraphs suggests that it could be relevant to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) research on graph-based machine learning and reasoning.
